    body     = "There's a difference between:\n\nBAD AD: wrong creative, wrong audience, wrong offer.\nWRONG CHANNEL: right creative, right audience, already saturated.\n\nThe second one is harder to spot.\n\nBecause your dashboards look fine.\n\nHere's the pattern I see repeatedly:\n\nA high-performing brand doubles down on their 'winning' channel.\nROAS is strong. Volume is good. Team is confident.\n\nBut over 2–3 quarters:\n→ CAC creeps up 15%... then 30%... then 50%\n→ New customer volume plateaus even with spend increases\n→ The channel is saturated but the dashboard doesn't say that\n\nHow to catch it early:\n\n1. Plot spend vs. new customers per month (not ROAS; new customers)\n   If spend goes up but new customers plateau → you're saturating\n\n2. Run a spend holdback test (reduce spend 20% for 4 weeks)\n   If results drop proportionally → not saturated\n   If results barely change → you're past the saturation point\n\n3. Model it with Robyn\n   The saturation curve will tell you exactly where the inflection point is\n   And how much budget to reallocate to under-invested channels\n\nThe channels that are currently under-invested in most businesses:\n→ Email (organic, zero media cost)\n→ SEO/content (slow but compounds)\n→ Retargeting of warm audiences (not cold acquisition)\n\nBudget reallocation without changing a single creative.\nJust moving money to where the marginal returns are higher.",
