    body     = "Specifically, they ask:\n\n'What is our incrementality by channel?'\nNot: 'What is our ROAS?'\n\n'Which cohorts have the highest LTV and where did they come from?'\nNot: 'How many leads did we get this month?'\n\n'Where are we past saturation and wasting spend?'\nNot: 'How do we scale?'\n\n'Which content pages appear in the journeys of our best customers?'\nNot: 'Which blog post got the most traffic?'\n\nThe difference between these questions isn't sophistication.\n\nIt's whether you've built the infrastructure to answer them.\n\nThat infrastructure has 4 parts:\n\n1. Clean tracking (GA4 → BigQuery, UTMs in CRM)\n2. A unified data layer (all sources in one table)\n3. An attribution model (Robyn, Markov, or both)\n4. A decision process that actually uses the output\n\nMost teams have part 1 (barely).\nFew have part 2.\nAlmost none have parts 3 and 4.\n\nThe teams that do?\n\nThey don't guess where to increase budget.\nThey run the Robyn allocator and get an answer.\n\nThey don't guess why revenue dropped.\nThey run the model and decompose it by channel and baseline.\n\nThey don't guess which campaigns to scale.\nThey identify the channel with the most room before saturation.\n\nThat's not magic.\n\nThat's infrastructure.\n\nBuild it once.\nUse it for every decision after.",
