    body     = "I see agencies still using 'iOS14' as an excuse for bad performance.\n\nHere is the reality:\nUser-level tracking is never going back to how it was in 2019.\n\nSafari blocks third-party cookies.\nChrome is phasing them out.\nUsers opt-out of tracking.\n\nIf your entire attribution model requires a clean, unbroken cookie trail from an Instagram impression to a Shopify checkout...\nYour model is already obsolete.\n\nSo how do billion-dollar brands still measure ROI?\n\nThey stopped relying on tracking individual users.\nThey started modeling aggregate data.\n\n→ Shift from deterministic (MTA) to probabilistic (MMM).\n→ Look at total business revenue vs. total marketing spend by channel.\n→ Use geo-holdout tests instead of pixel tracking.\n\nThe math hasn't stopped working. You're just trying to use the wrong equation.\n\nYou don't need to track every user to know if your marketing is profitable.\nYou just need to measure the incrementality of your spend.",
