    body     = "This is the concept of 'Baseline Revenue'.\nAnd it's the biggest blind spot in modern performance marketing.\n\nBaseline revenue is what your business makes just by existing:\n→ Word of mouth\n→ Returning customers buying again naturally\n→ Organic search from brand equity built years ago\n→ Direct traffic from bookmarks\n\nIf your baseline revenue is $100k/month, and you spend $20k on ads to generate $120k in total revenue...\n\nYour ad platforms will try to claim credit for as much of that $120k as they can touch.\n\nMeta will say it drove $40k.\nGoogle will say it drove $50k.\nEmail will claim $30k.\n\nBut the reality?\nYour marketing only drove $20k incrementally.\n\nUntil you calculate your true baseline, you will always overvalue your paid media.\n\nRobyn (and other MMMs) separate baseline from incremental marketing revenue mathematically by analyzing seasonality, trend, and zero-spend periods.\n\nStop letting platforms grade their own homework.",
