    body     = "I had to do this for a SaaS client spending $2M a year on LinkedIn Ads.\n\nThe CMO loved the dashboard. It showed a $350 CPA.\n\nBut I had run the MMM, and I knew the real incremental CPA was closer to $1,200.\n\nIf I just walked in and said, 'Your dashboard is wrong,' I would have lost the room.\n\nHere is the script I used instead:\n\n'The platform is accurately reporting what it sees based on last-click. But we noticed a discrepancy between marketing-reported revenue and the CFO's bank deposits. I ran an incrementality model to see where the gap is coming from.'\n\nI didn't attack the dashboard.\nI framed the dashboard as 'one piece of the puzzle' that was currently blind to the bigger picture.\n\nThen, I showed the geo-test data:\nWe had accidentally paused LinkedIn in the UK for a month.\nUK revenue didn't drop. At all.\n\nThat was the proof.\n\nYou can't fight a dashboard with another dashboard.\nYou fight it with business reality.\n\nFind a natural experiment (a paused campaign, an out-of-stock product, a holiday) and show them the gap between what the platform reported and what actually happened to total revenue.\n\nThat's how you get buy-in for MMM.",
