    hook     = "'How much historical data do I actually need to run Robyn?'\n\nI get this DM three times a week. Here is the exact mathematical answer.",
    body     = "People think MMM requires 5 years of pristine, daily data from a Fortune 500 data warehouse.\n\nIt doesn't.\n\nBut it does require strict minimums to be statistically significant.\n\nHere is the golden rule for Robyn (and Prophet, the engine beneath it):\n\nMINIMUM REQUIREMENT:\n→ 2 full years of continuous data (104 weeks).\n\nWhy 2 years?\nBecause the model needs to understand seasonality.\nIf you only have 1 year of data, the model doesn't know if that massive spike in November was because your ads were amazing, or because it was Black Friday.\nIt needs to see Black Friday happen *twice* to separate the seasonal effect from the media effect.\n\nGRANULARITY:\n→ Daily or Weekly data.\n→ Monthly data is useless. (36 months = 36 rows of data. A machine learning model can't train on 36 rows).\n\nWHAT YOU ACTUALLY NEED TO PULL:\n1. Date (Daily/Weekly)\n2. Revenue or Conversions (The target variable)\n3. Spend by Channel A, B, C...\n4. Impressions/Clicks by Channel A, B, C...\n5. Context variables (Holidays, competitor pricing, out-of-stock days)\n\nIf you have 104 weeks of that, you are ready to build an MMM.\nIf you don't, start storing it today. You'll thank yourself in 2026.",
